1) Disable root user logins
2) Allow wrong passwords to only be entered 4 times 
3) Secure cron and at in /etc/cron.deny and /etc/at.deny
4) Close unessary ports 
5) Change ssh port
6) Encrypt transmited data whenever possible 
7) Minimize software to minimize vulnerabilities 
8) Run different network services on seperate systems
9) Configure security tools to improve system robustness (zone-based firewalls, SELinux, log analysis)
10) Use the principle of least privilage 
11) Create Script to update System
12) Enable an Intrusion Detection System 

